HEADWORD: Stabber
<hw>Stab"ber</hw> <pr>(st⟦acr⟧b"b⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>One who, or that which, stabs; a privy
murderer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A small marline spike; a
pricker.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stabbingly</ent>⟦br⟧
